kend host Guy Raz.', u' ', u'The way we think about \u2014 and treat \u2014 these behaviors is wrong, Pelsser says. "There is a paradigm shift needed. If a child is diagnosed ADHD, we should say, \'OK, we have got those symptoms, now let\'s start looking for a cause.\' "', u' ', u'\n', u'Article continues after ', u'sponsorship', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' ', u'\n', u'\n', u' ', u' ', u'Pelsser compares ADHD to eczema. "The skin is affected, but a lot of people get eczema because of a latex allergy or because they are eating a pineapple or strawberries."', u' ', u"According to Pelsser, 64 percent of children diagnosed with ADHD are actually experiencing a hypersensitivity to food. Researchers determined that by starting kids on a very elaborate diet, then restricting it over a few weeks' time.", u' ', u'"It\'s only five weeks," Pelsser says. "If it is the diet, then we start to find out which foods are causing the problems."', u' ', u'Teachers and doctors who worked with children in the study reported marked changes in behavior. "In fact, they were flabbergasted," Pelsser says.', u' ', u'"After the diet, they were just normal children with normal behavior," she says. No longer were they easily distracted or forgetful, and the temper tantrums subsided.', u' ', u'Some teachers said they never thought it would work, Pelsser says. "It was so strange," she says, "that a diet would change the behavior of a child as thoroughly as they saw it. It was a miracle, a teacher said."', u' ', u'But diet is not the solution for all children with ADHD, Pelsser cautions.', u' ', u'"In all children, we should start with diet research," she says. If a child\'s behavior doesn\'t change, then drugs may still be necessary. "But now we are giving them all drugs, and I think that\'s a huge mistake," she says.', u' ', u"Also, Pelsser warns, altering your child's diet without a doctor's supervision is inadvisable.", u' ', u'"We have got good news \u2014 that food is the main cause of ADHD," she says. "We\'ve got bad news \u2014 that we have to train physicians to monitor this procedure because it cannot be done by a physician who is not trained."', u'\n', u'\n', u'googleoff: index', u'\n', u'\n', u'Facebook', u'\n', u'Twitter', u'\n', u'\n', u'Google+', u'\n', u'\n', u' END CLASS="G-INTERACTIVEPOST" DATA-CONTENTURL="HTTP://WWW.NPR.ORG/2011/03/12/134456594/STUDY-DIET-MAY-HELP-ADHD-KIDS-MORE-THAN-DRUGS?UTM_CAMPAIGN=STORYSHARE&UTM_SOURCE=PLUS.GOOGLE.COM&UTM_MEDIUM=SOCIAL" DATA-CONTENTDEEPLINKID="/STORY/134456594" DATA-CLIENTID="54045534594.APPS.GOOGLEUSERCONTENT.COM" DATA-COOKIEPOLICY="HTTP://NPR.ORG" DATA-PREFILLTEXT="" DATA-CALLTOACTIONLABEL="LISTEN" DATA-CALLTOACTIONURL="HTTP://WWW.NPR.ORG/2011/03/12/134456594/STUDY-DIET-MAY-HELP-ADHD-KIDS-MORE-THAN-DRUGS?UTM_CAMPAIGN=STORYSHARE&UTM_SOURCE=PLUS.GOOGLE.COM&UTM_MEDIUM=SOCIAL" DATA-CALLTOACTIONDEEPLINKID="/STORY/LISTEN/134456594" ', u'\n', u'\n', u'Email', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' END CLASS="SHARE-TOOLS SHARE-TOOLS--SECONDARY" ARIA-LABEL="SHARE TOOLS" ', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' END ID="NEWSLETTER-ACQUISITION-CALLOUT-DATA" DATA-NEWSLETTER="{&QUOT;NEWSLETTERID&QUOT;:&QUOT;BEST-OF-NPR&QUOT;,&QUOT;TITLE&QUOT;:&QUOT;BEST OF NPR&QUOT;,&QUOT;MARKETINGHEADER&QUOT;:&QUOT;GET THE STORIES THAT GRABBED US THIS WEEK&QUOT;,&QUOT;FREQUENCY&QUOT;:&QUOT;EVERY WEEK&QUOT;,&QUOT;SHORTDESCRIPTION&QUOT;:&QUOT;DELIVERED TO YOUR INBOX EVERY SUNDAY, THESE ARE THE NPR STORIES THAT KEEP US SCROLLING.&QUOT;,&QUOT;CONTENTIMAGE&QUOT;:&QUOT;HTTP:\\/\\/MEDIA.NPR.ORG\\/ASSETS\\/IMG\\/2015\\/10\\/13\\/BESTOF-NEWSLETTER_CUSTOM.PNG&QUOT;,&QUOT;STATICMARKUPDIR&QUOT;:&QUOT;&QUOT;,&QUOT;BRANDINGDIR&QUOT;:&QUOT;&QUOT;,&QUOT;BRANDINGLINK&QUOT;:&QUOT;HTTP:\\/\\/WWW.MEDIA.NPR.ORG\\/ASSETS\\/IMG\\/2015\\/09\\/21\\/MOST-EMAILED_CUSTOM.PNG&QUOT;}" ', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' END ID="CALLOUT-END-OF-STORY-MOUNT" ', u'\n', u'\n', u' END ID="END-OF-STORY-RECOMMENDATIONS-MOUNT" CLASS="RECOMMENDED-STORIES" ARIA-LABEL="RECOMMENDED STORIES" ', u'\n', u' ', 